<%- include('partials/head', { title: 'The problem' }) %>
<%- include('partials/nav') %>

<div class="page">
<section class="page-section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="page-header a-fade-up">
      <div class="section-tag">The problem</div>
      <h2>Auto-renewal isn't an accident. It's the business model.</h2>
      <p>Every provider you deal with is incentivised to make renewal silent and cancellation slow. The cost shows up months later, buried in a bank statement you don't read line by line. perch. turns the invisible into something you can actually see — and act on.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="traps a-fade-up traps-a">
      <div class="trap">
        <span class="trap-num">01</span>
        <h3>Car insurance auto-renewal</h3>
        <p>Your premium jumps 20–40% at renewal because insurers know most people won't shop around. The "loyalty penalty" is well documented and entirely legal. perch. catches the price change and tells you before it hits your bank.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="trap">
        <span class="trap-num">02</span>
        <h3>Domain lapses</h3>
        <p>A domain you registered three years ago for a side project quietly expires, gets scooped by a squatter, and now costs ten times more to get it back — if that's even possible. perch. flags it with weeks to spare, not hours.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="trap">
        <span class="trap-num">03</span>
        <h3>Broadband out-of-contract pricing</h3>
        <p>Once your fixed term ends, providers move you to a higher "out of contract" rate by default. No warning that feels urgent enough to act on. perch. shows you the before and after so you know exactly what the switch is costing you.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="page-section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="page-header a-fade-up">
      <div class="section-tag">Who it hits hardest</div>
      <h2>Two kinds of overwhelm, one tool.</h2>
      <p>Different scale, same problem: things renew that shouldn't, and the admin overhead of tracking them isn't anyone's job — until it costs money.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="audience a-fade-up">
      <div class="audience-card">
        <h3>Households</h3>
        <div class="sub">Earning £40k–£90k, juggling more renewals than time to track them</div>
        <ul>
          <li>Car, home, and pet insurance renewals</li>
          <li>Broadband and mobile contract end dates</li>
          <li>Streaming, gym, and app subscriptions</li>
          <li>Personal domains and annual services</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="audience-card">
        <h3>Small businesses</h3>
        <div class="sub">1–5 person teams with no dedicated ops or admin support</div>
        <ul>
          <li>SaaS tool renewals across the whole stack</li>
          <li>Business insurance and liability cover</li>
          <li>Domain and hosting renewals</li>
          <li>Vendor and supplier contract deadlines</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="page-section not-section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="page-header a-fade-up">
      <div class="section-tag">What we explicitly don't do</div>
      <h2>If it sounds like a budgeting app, that's the wrong app.</h2>
      <p>perch. has one job: tell you what's about to renew and what to do about it. That's it. No feature creep, no dashboard you'll never open, no ads dressed up as "insights."</p>
    </div>
    <div class="not-grid a-fade-up">
      <div class="not-card">
        <div class="not-mark">✕</div>
        <h3>No bank linking</h3>
        <p>We never connect to your bank or card accounts. We work from documents and emails you choose to send us — nothing else. No read-only access, no "just this once" permission, no fine print.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-card">
        <div class="not-mark">✕</div>
        <h3>No auto-cancel bots</h3>
        <p>We don't act on your behalf, ever. You get the verdict and the deadline. You make the call and take the action. We're a radar, not a robot with your login credentials.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-card">
        <div class="not-mark">✕</div>
        <h3>No budgeting features</h3>
        <p>No spend categories, no net worth tracking, no charts about your coffee habit. That's a different product, built by someone else. We stay in our lane — renewals only, done well.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
